(516, '_transient_dash_4077549d03da2e451c8b5f002294ff51', '<div class="rss-widget"><ul><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wordpress.org/news/2013/07/annual-wordpress-survey-wcsf/'' title=''It‚Äôs time for our third annual user and developer survey! If you‚Äôre a WordPress user, developer, or business, we want your feedback. Just like previous years, we‚Äôll share the data at the upcoming WordCamp San Francisco (WCSF). Results will also be sent to each survey respondent. It only takes a few minutes to fill out [‚Ä¶] [&hellip;]''>Annual WordPress Survey &amp; WCSF</a> <span class="rss-date">July 9, 2013</span><div class=''rssSummary''>It‚Äôs time for our third annual user and developer survey! If you‚Äôre a WordPress user, developer, or business, we want your feedback. Just like previous years, we‚Äôll share the data at the upcoming WordCamp San Francisco (WCSF). Results will also be sent to each survey respondent. It only takes a few minutes to fill out [‚Ä¶] [&hellip;]</div></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wordpress.org/news/2013/06/wordpress-3-5-2/'' title=''WordPress 3.5.2 is now available. This is the second maintenance release of 3.5, fixing 12 bugs.¬†This is a security release for all previous versions and we strongly encourage you to update your sites immediately. The WordPress security team resolved seven security issues, and this release also contains some additional security hardening. The security fixes  [&hellip;]''>WordPress 3.5.2 Maintenance and Security Release</a> <span class="rss-date">June 21, 2013</span><div class=''rssSummary''>WordPress 3.5.2 is now available. This is the second maintenance release of 3.5, fixing 12 bugs.¬†This is a security release for all previous versions and we strongly encourage you to update your sites immediately. The WordPress security team resolved seven security issues, and this release also contains some additional security hardening. The security fixes  [&hellip;]</div></li></ul></div>', 'no'),
